                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d519">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">713.1311/246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-17T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 17, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>11. We assume that the attitude of the Guatemalan Government as reported in
                    Lawton’s telegram of last night that the transmission of its draft proposals to
                    the other Governments “makes it less important to hurry the opening of the
                    Conference” takes care of the situation mentioned in your 52, February 16, 3
                    p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
